description.value: Bronze lamp-stand: tripod foot with lion's legs, much mended and one paw damaged; they converge on a ring-housing for the tapered tenon of the separately made fluted shaft, the top of which is broken away. The tenon of the shaft was brazed onto the foot in antiquity. A circular plate, now loose and broken in two, was once placed above the foot, supported by collar, also loose. The upper surface of the plate is divided into concentric bands, the inner one engraved with Bacchic features, including masks, thyrsoi and a syrinx. This frieze is surrounded by a narrow kymation band and an outer band with tendrils; the downturned rim is decorated with simple ovolos. A modern brass disc has now been soldered onto the tip of the tenon, to put less strain on the repairs.

description.value: Januari 2010 during conservation treatment.  Brass pricket lampstand with three rounded feet and short legs supporting a flaring lower element decorated with horizontal grooves. The lower circumference has six knobs, one above each leg and the others spaced equidistantly between them; each leg is strengthened by a strut behind it. At the top of the lower element is a baluster holding the shaft, which apparently extends right through the lower element, showing as a knob on its underside. The shaft, which thickens in the middle and tapers again to its top, is seven sided. At the top is another baluster, holding the pricket; the latter tapers from a rounded section to square. Heavily corroded. Surface coloration: patchy dark and light green, with large turquoise-coloured areas at the bottom.

The lower circumference has six knobs, one above each leg and the others spaced equidistantly between them; each leg is strengthened by a strut behind it. At the top of the lower element is a baluster holding the shaft, which apparently extends right through the lower element, showing as a knob on its underside. The shaft, which thickens in the middle and tapers again to its top, is seven sided. At the top is another baluster, holding the pricket; the latter tapers from a rounded section to square. Heavily corroded. Surface coloration: patchy dark and light green, with large turquoise-coloured areas at the bottom. Before conservation.
